$$
\begin{aligned}
F &=\left(m_{\text {rope }}+m_{\text {gatellite }}\right) \cdot a \\
&=(950+50) \times 5=5 \times 10^{3} \mathrm{~N} .
\end{aligned}
$$Choose the point where the rope is attached to the satellite as the origin and the $x$-axis along the rope towards the spaceship. The tension along the rope is then

$$
\begin{aligned}
F(x) &=\left(m_{\text {satellite }}+m_{\text {rope }}(x)\right) \cdot a \\
